The barrel shifter can also be used for register operands too, of course. In the simplest example, you can write rrxs r0, r1 or movs r0, r1, rrx to perform a 33-bit rotate of the register. In this specific case, you don’t need an rlx shift, as you can write adcs r1, r0, r0 instead.